<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1823,2029]" lastBlockId="20.[151,1436,151,429]" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="21" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,350,2003,2029]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Rediagnosis.</emphasis>
Recognized by its moderate size; dark reddish brown general coloration; almost linear antennal segment II that is weakly clavate; nearly straight metatibia; C-shaped endosoma with bifurcate median process (its shorter branch tiny, 
<figureCitation box="[372,471,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1788,1812]" captionTargetBox="[173,1401,286,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-61@23.[164,1423,273,1765]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 11. Male endosoma (vesica) and endosoma of Japanese Pilophorus spp. A. P. choii (from Otaru). B. P. erraticus (Nagasaki). C. P. pseudoperplexus (Kanagawa). D. P.okamotoi (Tsushima Is.). E. P.satoyamanus n. sp. (Kochi).F. P.setulosellus n. sp. (Hiroshima). G. Same (Nara). H. P. setulosus (Sapporo, type locality, Salix). I. Same, (Shiretoko, Artemisia)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596059" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4596059/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 11C</figureCitation>
); sclerotized ring with a developed rim dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[1015,1117,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1859,1883]" captionTargetBox="[167,1419,463,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-137@25.[164,1423,453,1836]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 12. Female bursa copulatrix and eggs (B, E, H) of Japanese Pilophorus spp. A, C, F, K–L. Dorsal view. D, G, I, J, M. Ventral view, with vestibular sclerite (VES). A–B. P. erraticus (Nagasaki). C–E. P. pseudoperplexus (Otaru). F–H. P. satoyamanus n. sp. (Ibaraki). I. P. okamotoi (Tsushima Is.). J–K. P. setulosellus n. sp. (Hiroshima). L–M. P. setulosus (Asahikawa)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4596061/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 12C</figureCitation>
); and vestibular sclerite with a conical projection left-laterally (
<figureCitation box="[533,637,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1859,1883]" captionTargetBox="[167,1419,463,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-137@25.[164,1423,453,1836]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 12. Female bursa copulatrix and eggs (B, E, H) of Japanese Pilophorus spp. A, C, F, K–L. Dorsal view. D, G, I, J, M. Ventral view, with vestibular sclerite (VES). A–B. P. erraticus (Nagasaki). C–E. P. pseudoperplexus (Otaru). F–H. P. satoyamanus n. sp. (Ibaraki). I. P. okamotoi (Tsushima Is.). J–K. P. setulosellus n. sp. (Hiroshima). L–M. P. setulosus (Asahikawa)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4596061/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 12D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
